4 A RESOLUTION OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF MONTANA ENCOURAGING
5 ALL STATEWIDE ELECTED OFFICIALS IN MONTANA TO HOLD AT LEAST TWO PUBLICLY NOTICED
6 TOWN HALL MEETINGS EACH YEAR WITH AN OPEN OPPORTUNITY FOR THE PUBLIC TO ASK
7 QUESTIONS.
8
9 WHEREAS, Article II, section 1, of the Montana Constitution states, "All political power is vested in and
10 derived from the people. All government of right originates with the people, is founded upon their will only, and
11 is instituted solely for the good of the whole"; and
12 WHEREAS, Montana holds free and fair elections to elect officials to all levels of public office, from
13 local government officials, to the state legislature, to the United States Congress; and
14 WHEREAS, it is the job of elected officials to represent their constituents; and
15 WHEREAS, town hall meetings provide the opportunity for elected officials to discuss specific topics of
16 public interest, to hear directly from their constituents, and to answer questions from their communities.
17
18 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
19 MONTANA:
20 That all statewide elected officials in Montana be encouraged to hold publicly noticed town hall
21 meetings for all of their constituents at least twice a year with an open opportunity for the public to ask
22 questions to maintain a healthy dialogue and to stay connected to the ideas, concerns, and needs of their
23 communities.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State send a copy of this resolution to each elected
25 official in the state of Montana.
